🏗 Section 9: Operational Governance & Delivery Discipline

Role & Purpose in the Manual
	•	This is the execution control plane of the manual: the suite of rituals, routines, dashboards, metrics maturity, and escalations that turn principles into lived practice.
	•	It details how governance happens in practice (daily to monthly), linking the tactics in requirements, debt, quality, and commercial tracks into a coherent operating rhythm.
	•	It ensures that the manual isn’t just aspirational: this section gives the playbook for daily discipline, team routines, metrics enforcement, and continuous improvement.

Because many delivery failures come not from lacking ideas, but from poor execution discipline — this section helps the reader operationalize all prior theory.

⸻

🎯 Promise: What Section 9 Will Deliver

By the end of Section 9, the reader will:
	•	Have a tiered catalog of rituals (daily, weekly, sprint-end, monthly, quarterly) with purpose, participants, inputs/outputs, metrics, and pitfalls.
	•	Understand how to conduct the “flight check” (project readiness setup) to validate that all governance tools, dashboards, ledgers, and pipelines are in place.
	•	Be able to scale metrics maturity: how to progress from manual data collection → automated dashboards → predictive alerts.
	•	Know how to design role-based dashboards & alerts, their frequencies, escalation paths, and visibility audiences.
	•	Be equipped to maintain a playbook template for operations that the entire delivery team can refer to and adapt.
	•	Learn how governance rituals feed into steering and commercial forums — closing the loop between execution and strategy.

In short: this section makes the rest of the manual achievable — operational discipline is the backbone that holds all the guardrails together.

